      "text": " On the other hand, the first order PDE (62) is the same of the zero order one but with the addition of the source term  $F(\\eta, \\pi_k)$ . In order to solve it, we consider that the eigenfunctions  $\\psi_n(\\eta, \\pi_k)$  form a complete orthonormal basis such that  $\\langle \\psi_{n_1} | \\psi_{n_2} \\rangle = \\delta_{n_1,n_2}$  and any function can be expressed as a linear combination of them. Therefore we can write  $\\psi^1$  and  $\\psi^0$  as",
